Are you inspired by invention? Is problem solving through teamwork in your DNA? We apply advances in robotics and software to solve real-world problems that delight our customers' experiences in ways we can't even imagine yet.
 
Amazon Robotics is located in the greater Boston area, the epicenter of robotics innovation. Our diverse team of engineers come from all over the world to design, test and build our dynamic fleet of robots and mechatronic systems. Having our offices, labs, test floors and factories all co-located means that we can design the hardware, write the code, test, build and watch it all come to life. This allows us to innovate quickly and on limitless ideas. Current advancements are underway in autonomous movement and mobility, artificial intelligence and machine learning, manipulation, simulation, robotic management software, predictive analytics, and much more.
 
The Customer Service Program Specialist - Demand Management will be responsible for generating and maintaining demand signals through a dynamic, cross-functional change management process connecting site requirements with delivery schedules to enable other cross functional teams to execute on the demand signal. They will work with both internal and external stakeholders including but not limited to customers, engineering, purchasing, quality, logistics, installation, and field service. A successful candidate will have tactical experience of order management, customer service, and supply chain.
 
The Customer Service Program Specialist's primary responsibilities will include, but not be limited to:
 
 Enter, manage, and administer all sales orders activity in our ERP system including data entry, updates, monitoring and reporting for portfolio of customers. 
 Engage cross functional teams on confirming BOMâ€™s, return material authorizations, receiving material commits, and delivery options. 
 Prioritize daily tasks between urgent customer needs and long term strategic plans. 
 Ensure proper PO coverage is provided for orders, research shortages to prevent delays. 
 Manage expectations on delivery issues and escalations with install team and manager. 
 Perform supply and demand inventory analysis to ensure timely shipments. 
 Maintain and update personal site tracking lists as sites are added, removed, and rescheduled. 
 Create and administer inter-team process improvement tools to increase efficiency. 
 Manage and maintain internal orders for company employees through requisition system. 
 Expert in Microsoft Excel, Word and PowerPoint. 
 Analyzing and Understanding of metrics and process capabilities 
 2+ years of customer service experience 
 2+ years of business intelligence tools experience 
 2+ years of modeling in Microsoft Excel/Tableau 
 2+ years of experience or Oracle or equipment ERP system 
 
